                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Titagarh Wagons in pact talks
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Chowdhary in Calcutta on Friday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury                                  
	Calcutta, Aug. 27: Titagarh Wagons Ltd is in talks with a Japanese firm to build rail-road infrastructure such as bridges and flyovers in India.        
	Chairman J.P. Chowdhary said the negotiations would be completed within a month or two.         
	It could be a separate joint venture or even a technology transfer, he said.        
	Speaking on the sidelines of the companys annual general meeting, he said the new outfit, which was likely to be an associate of Titagarh Wagons, would use the companys existing infrastructure.        
	On the market for bridges and flyovers, he said, The opportunity is huge.         
	Titagarh is one of the largest wagon makers in India with a capacity of 5,000 units. It co-owns Cimmco along with the SK Birla group, which can manufacture another 5,000.                                                                                                                                                                
